Explanation:
We use a 256-element array to store the count of each character in the string. We iterate through the string and update the count for each character. If the count exceeds 2, we reset the count and update the starting index for the next iteration. Finally, we keep track of the maximum length of the substring found so far and return it. The time complexity is O(n) because we iterate through the string once. The space complexity is O(1) because we only use a fixed-size array for the count. The energy implications are low because the algorithm only requires a small amount of energy to run.

